<s> Yes. To summarize the possible variations: 1) specify that a MOVE inside a collection does not add a new member - in this case a "rename" operation won't change ordering, but will be completely inconsistent with the cross-collection MOVE (where a new member *is* added and thus the Position header semantics apply) 2) specify that a MOVE inside a collection removes the old and adds a new member - consistency with cross-collection MOVE operation, but ordering will be lost when done by a client that isn't aware of ordering semantics 3) do not mandate a specific behaviour (the current wording) -- in which case we'd still need to decide whether spec needs to be more specific about this being server-defined behaviour.  </s>
<s> I think in doubt we should consider simplicity of the spec as well, therefore leave things as they are and possibly make that more explicit.  </s>
<s> Julian  </s>
